text: Witherslack is a village and civil parish in South Lakeland, Cumbria, England. In 2001 there were 482 people living in Witherslack. It has 15 listed buildings. It has a church called St Paul's, which was built in about 1669. == References == Category:Villages in Cumbria Category:Civil parishes in Cumbria
